 :tx/rationale "Set t-e9471f3a title=ACP-DRY-2: Cache calibration metrics per command invocation. compute_calibration_metrics is called 2x per command: once in compute_routing_from_store (routing.rs) for task confidence, once in methodology_context_blocks (context.rs) for block confidence. The hypothesis scan is O(H*K) where H=hypotheses, K=types. APPROACH: (1) Create CalibrationSnapshot struct: CalibrationReport + timestamp. (2) In compute_routing_from_store, compute calibration once and store in the returned RoutingResult. (3) Change methodology_context_blocks signature to accept &CalibrationReport parameter instead of computing its own. (4) In status.rs (the main caller), pass the calibration from routing result to context blocks. (5) Other callers that only need one or the other continue to work unchanged. ACCEPTANCE: (A) compute_calibration_metrics called exactly once per command (verifiable by logging or test instrumentation). (B) CalibrationReport values identical whether cached or recomputed. (C) No public API breakage — callers that don't pass calibration get auto-computed (backward compat). (D) Performance: braid status on large store (>50K datoms) measurably faster. TRACES: ADR-FOUNDATION-019. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs + context.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs"
